Dole ne Amurka ta biya I.A. sau biyu
Yayin da kasar Sin ke kara samun karfin gwiwa a fannin kere kere, Amurka ta kamata ta kara kashe kudade wajen binciken wannan fannin, a cewar Kai-Fu Lee, wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Maganar ta zo ne yayin da bangarori da dama na gwamnatin Amurka suka yi ikirarin AI, duk da cewa Amurka ba ta da sanannen shirin AI.
A gefe guda kuma, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirinta a bara: tana son zama kasa ta 1 a cikin kirkirar AI kafin shekarar 2030.
"Tashi biyu na kudaden bincike na AI zai zama kyakkyawan farawa, tabbas sauran kasashen sun kai matakin da Amurka ta dauka, amma muna neman abin mamaki na gaba a AI", in ji Lee.
Tattara kudade sau biyu na iya haifar da babbar dama kuma ci gaban AI na gaba zai kasance a Amurka, Lee ya fada wa CNBC a cikin wata hira a wannan makon.
Lee, wanda littafinsa AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order aka buga a wannan watan ta Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, shi ne Shugaba na Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a cikin babbar kamfanin AI na kasar Sin, Face++.
A 1980s a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon ya yi aiki a kan tsarin AI wanda ya lashe kyautar Othello a Amurka, daga bisani ya zama shugaban kamfanin Microsoft Research da kuma shugaban kamfanin Google a kasar Sin.
Lee ya amince da gasar fasaha ta gwamnatin Amurka kamar ta Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency's Robotics Challenge kuma ya tambayi lokacin da za a yi na gaba, don taimakawa wajen gano sababbin masu fafatawa a gaba.
Lee ya ce masu bincike a Amirka sukan yi aiki tuƙuru don su sami goyon bayan gwamnati.
"Ba kasar Sin ba ce ke kwace ikon jami'an ilimi; masana'antu ne", in ji Lee.
Facebook, Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha suna daukar kwararru daga jami'o'i don yin aiki a kan AI a cikin 'yan shekarun nan.
Lee ya ce sauye-sauyen dokokin shige da fice na iya taimaka wa Amurka wajen tallafawa kokarinta na AI.
"Ina ganin ya kamata a ba da katin kore ga masu PhD a AI ta atomatik", in ji shi.
Majalisar Jiha ta kasar Sin ta fitar da Shirin Ci gaban Ilimin Halitta na gaba a watan Yulin 2017.
