HIV/Carrosis: China ta samu kashi 14% na sabbin cututtuka
Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa tana fuskantar matsalar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar sankara.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne suka kamu a ƙasar.
An samu karuwar sabbin maganganu 40,000 a kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin waɗannan sababbin kalmomin sun samo asali ne daga jima'i, suna nuna canji a dā.
A al'adance, cutar HIV ta yadu cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar jini da aka yi amfani da shi daga mutanen da suka kamu da cutar.
Amma adadin masu kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa zero, in ji jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron da aka gudanar a yankin Yunnan.
Ko da yake, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar sankarar bargo sun ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i ta zama babban batu a tsakanin LGBT na kasar Sin.
An soke cin zarafin jinsi daya a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna wa LGBT wariya.
Saboda dokokin tsaro na ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na mazajen da suke yin luwadi za su yi aure.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne ta hanyar rashin yin jima'i a cikin waɗannan abokan.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV da ake kira ozurumba a matsayin wani mataki na magance matsalar.
