Yayin da wasu shugabannin jam'iyyar Republican suka goyi bayan Brett Kavanaugh wanda ya zabi shi a matsayin babban alkalin kotun kasar, masu bincike sun yi gargadin cewa za a samu tashin hankali, musamman daga mata, a lokacin zaben da za a yi a lokacin da za a yi zaben.
An samu karɓuwa sosai, kuma an rubuta cewa yawancin 'yan Republican sun nuna sha'awar su ci gaba da zaɓen.
Ba za a iya dawo da abubuwan ba, Grant Reeher, farfesa a fannin kimiyyar siyasa a Jami'ar Syracuse Maxwell School ya yi magana da The Hill game da labarin da aka buga a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana kalubalantar matakin da dan majalisar Jeff Flake (R-Arizona) ya dauka na karshe na gudanar da bincike na FBI da zai isa ya rage fushin masu jefa kuri'a.
 Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru jiya ba - ba za su manta da gobe ba sai Nuwamba,  Karine Jean-Pierre, babban mai ba da shawara kuma kakakin al'umma don ƙungiyar ci gaba ta MoveOn ya ce a ranar Juma'a, bisa ga jaridar Washington, D.C.
A safiyar ranar Juma'a, masu zanga-zanga sun yi ta rera waƙar "Nuwamba na zuwa!" yayin da suke zagayawa a duk hanyar da ta kai majalisar dokoki inda 'yan Republican suka yi zabe a babban taron majalisa don ci gaba da zaben Kavanaugh duk da ikirarin Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, Mic.
"Himma da kuma motsawar 'yan Democrat za su kasance na musamman", Stu Rothenberg, wani mai bincike kan siyasa da ya yi aiki tare da shi ya shaida wa manema labarai.
